enaline reuptake only","Blocks reuptake of serotonin and noradrenaline"],"correctOptions":[4],"correctResponses":null,"explanation":"\u003Cp\u003EThe primary mechanism of action of venlafaxine and other Serotonin and noradrenaline reuptake inhibitors (SNRIs )is through \u003Cstrong\u003Eblocking reuptake of serotonin and noradrenaline\u003C/strong\u003E at the synaptic cleft.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EBlocking histamine and muscarinic receptors\u003C/strong\u003E and \u003Cstrong\u003Eantagonising alpha-1 adrenergic receptors\u003C/strong\u003E are characteristic actions of tricyclic antidepressants, causing side effects like sedation and postural hypotension. Unlike tricyclic antidepressants, SNRIs have minimal activity at other receptor sites, leading to fewer side effects. \u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EBlocking dopamine D2 receptors\u003C/strong\u003E is the primary mechanism of action of typical antipsychotic medications. \u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EInhibition of noradrenaline reuptake only\u003C/strong\u003E would describe selective noradrenaline reuptake inhibitors (NRIs) like reboxetine, but not SNRIs which have dual action.\u003C/p\u003E","optionExplanations":["","","","",""],"learningPoints":["Serotonin and noradrenaline reuptake inhibitors (SNRIs) block the reuptake of both serotonin and noradrenaline in the synaptic cleft, but with greater selectivity than tricyclic antidepressants.","Venlafaxine is a commonly prescribed Serotonin and noradrenaline reuptake inhibitors (SNRI) used to treat depression and anxiety disorders.","Serotonin and noradrenaline reuptake inhibitors (SNRIs) have fewer side effects than tricyclic antidepressants due to their more selective binding profile."],"references":["Therapeutic Guidelines. Melbourne: Therapeutic Guidelines Limited. Available from: https://www.tg.org.au","Australian Medicines Handbook\u00a0(online). Adelaide: Australian Medicines Handbook Pty Ltd. Available from: